  "prompt": "Which Indian startup is looking for funding in 2017?",
  "response": "In 2017, the Indian startup ecosystem was vibrant and rapidly growing, with numerous companies seeking funding to scale their operations. Some notable Indian startups looking for funding during that year included:\n\n1. **UrbanClap (now Urban Company):**\n   - **Sector:** On-demand home services\n   - **Overview:** UrbanClap aimed to connect users with various service professionals, such as plumbers, electricians, beauticians, and more, through a mobile app and website platform.\n   - **Funding Activity:** In 2017, UrbanClap raised significant funding to expand its services to more cities and enhance its technology infrastructure.\n\n2. **Razorpay:**\n   - **Sector:** Fintech (Payment Solutions)\n   - **Overview:** Razorpay provided online payment gateways and solutions for businesses to accept, process, and disburse payments.\n   - **Funding Activity:** The startup secured funding in 2017 to fuel its growth in the competitive payment processing market in India.\n\n3. **Pepperfry:**\n   - **Sector:** E-commerce (Furniture and Home Decor)\n   - **Overview:** Pepperfry specialized in selling furniture and home decor products online, aiming to make furniture shopping convenient and accessible.\n   - **Funding Activity:** In 2017, Pepperfry raised capital to expand its inventory, improve logistics, and enhance customer experience.\n\n4. **Lenskart:**\n   - **Sector:** E-commerce (Eyewear)\n   - **Overview:** Lenskart offered a wide range of eyewear products, including glasses, contact lenses, and sunglasses, both online and through physical stores.\n   - **Funding Activity:** The company attracted investment in 2017 to scale its operations and increase its market penetration across India.\n\n5. **Paperboat:**\n   - **Sector:** Food & Beverage (Traditional Drinks)\n   - **Overview:** Paperboat focused on producing traditional Indian beverages with a modern twist, emphasizing authentic flavors and nostalgic branding.\n   - **Funding Activity:** In 2017, Paperboat raised funds to boost production capacity and expand its distribution network.\n\n6. **OYO Rooms:**\n   - **Sector:** Hospitality (Budget Hotels)\n   - **Overview:** OYO aimed to standardize and provide affordable accommodation across India and internationally through its network of partner hotels.\n   - **Funding Activity:** OYO secured substantial funding in 2017 to accelerate its expansion plans and enhance its technological platform.\n\n7. **Innov8:**\n   - **Sector:** Co-working Spaces\n   - **Overview:** Innov8 offered collaborative workspaces tailored to startups, freelancers, and businesses seeking flexible office environments.\n   - **Funding Activity:** The startup raised funds in 2017 to open new locations and improve its service offerings.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and many other startups across various sectors were actively seeking and securing funding in 2017 to capitalize on India's burgeoning market and entrepreneurial spirit. If you're interested in a specific industry or a particular startup, feel free to ask for more detailed information!",
